{"word":"κικλήσκω","slug":"κικλήσκω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κικλήσκω</b></el> <el>(κικλήσκω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:poetically'>poet.</a> <a href='S:reduplication'>redupl.</a> form of <a href='S:καλέω'><el>καλέω</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to call, summon</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to call on, invoke, implore</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to accost, address</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>to name, call by name</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>: —<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>νῆσός τις Συρίη κικλήσκεται</el> <i>there is</i> an island <i>called</i> Syros, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <el>κλῄζω</el> II.<p/></div>"}]}